data.content:
Three things break. Here's each one and the fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` ŌĆö no longer accepts expression trees

The parameter changed from `Expression<Func<...>>` to `Func<...>`. Your manual expression tree code won't compile. Replace it with a simple lambda:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

All that `Expression.Lambda`/`Expression.Call` machinery is no longer needed.

---

### 2. Complex type columns ŌĆö two changes

**a) Shared names are now uniquified.** `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` previously silently shared one column; now they get `Street` and `Street1`. To keep the old behavior, pin names explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
});
```

**b) Nested complex types now use the full path.** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` was previously `BillingAddress_City`; it's now `Payment_BillingAddress_City`. To preserve the old name:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

ŌÜĀ’ĖÅ Both changes affect **existing migrations/databases** ŌĆö generate a new migration and verify the diff, or pin column names to avoid schema churn.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` ŌĆö new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gains a `string logCommandText` parameter (contains redacted SQL for logging). Add it to your implementation:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ŌåÉ new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (sensitive data redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for the actual executed SQL
    }
}
```

Update **all** methods on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) the same way.
